The CJS Standard Library

stdfile - the filesystem handler.

stdio - the STANDARD INPUT OUTPUT, put this at the top of your modules.

stdprefix - functions for prepending to strings.

dir/  - Contains files for working with directory information.

debug/ - Contains debugging tools such as assert(expr)

algo/ - contains functions for doing continuous operations (such as, foreach instead of classical for)

math/ - Contains mathematical functions / consts.

HOW TO INSTALL:

You can embed this into your project by placing the include directory in the same dir as your .cjs file,

Or you can use the installer to install the CJS standard library onto your computer.

This repository also doubles as the CJS download site, go to releases to find setup binaries for the CJS language, and the CJS library